result.text:
One of the most important concepts in trading is figuring out in which conditions you perform best and when you don't.

To realize this further just run the math behind when you trade in good conditions vs bad.

Then, do the math about how losses make it more difficult to come back overall.

A 50% drawdown means you need a 100% upside move to return to breakeven.

An 80% drawdown means you need a 400% upside move to return to breakeven.

Limit losses by all means and trade when you have the layup.
